To solve for the pretax cost savings, we will use the formula for the net present value:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net present value}&=-\text{Initial investment}-\text{Net working capital}\\
&+\text{Present value of cash flow}
\end{aligned}$$

For the present value of cash flow, we must first get the operating cash flow per year using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Operating cash flow}&=(\text{Pretax cost savings})\times(1-\text{Tax rate})+\text{Tax rate}\times \text{Depreciation}
\end{aligned}$$

To get the present value of the cash flow, we will use this formula. The annuity factor that we will multiply is $3.8897$

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value cash flow}&=\left[(\text{Pretax cost savings})\times0.78\times3.8897+\text{Tax rate}\times\left(\dfrac{\text{year 1 cash flow}}{(1-\text{required return})^1}+...+\dfrac{\text{year 4 cash flow}}{(1-\text{required return})^4}\right)\right]\\
&+\dfrac{\text{Net working capital}+\text{After tax salvage value}}{(1+\text{required return})^5}
\end{aligned}$$
